    <event event_id="macro_ready"><![CDATA[<p>Called when the view parameters for the drop down have been set. You can use this to modify the macro name, content, html content, as well as whether or not the select box will be displayed.</p>

<p>Callback signature:</p>
<blockquote><code><em>array</em> &$macros, &$canviewmacros, $thread, array $forum, $type</code></blockquote>

<p>Arguments:</p>
<ol>
	<li><code><em>array</em> &$macros</code> - array of macro arrays being passed to the selector.</li>
	<li><code><em>boolean</em> &$canviewmacros</code> - if false, the selector will not be shown.</li>
	<li><code><em>array|null</em> $thread</code> - thread array. Only available if the first part of the <code>$type</code> variable is not convo.</li>
	<li><code><em>array</em> $forum</code> - forum array. Only available if the first part of the <code>$type</code> variable is not convo.</li>
	<li><code><em>string</em> $type</code> - type string. Pertains to the location of the qr editor requested. Will either be qr (for quick reply), ntnr (new thread, new reply), convoqr (conversation quick reply) or convoncnr (conversation new conversation, new reply).
</ol>]]></event>
